<br>
::when they are about 15 feet from Hades, they put the carrier down gently and the royal head gaurd walks to her from Hades, bows and holds her hand delicately as she takes his and steps out. The royal gaurd escorts her regally to Hades and bows and steps to the side and turns facing Hades' left. Persephone lowers her head and bows to the ground and slowly rises, keeping her head down:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/2/01 8:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Queen's Arrival</span><hr size=1> ::Hades bows his head slightly to his queen before extending his hand, to accept her into his Palace again.  He places her hand into his and bid her to rise.  His eyes and face solemn before all present.  The then turned with Persephone and walked her into the Palace.  Once the presence of all servants vanished, Hades smiled.  A smile of happiness for the first time in a long time.  Though he didn't show it most of the time, he did miss his bride.  He escorted her to the throne room before whispering into her ear::<br>
